claims:
1. A method for processing biomass comprising:
      Irradiating cellulosic or lignocellulosic material to provide a reduced recalcitrance lignocellulosic or cellulosic material;
      saccharifying the reduced recalcitrance lignocellulosic or cellulosic material with one or more enzymes to obtain a sugar solution comprising a mixture of sugars including glucose and/or xylose;
      fermenting the sugar solution with an organism that selectively ferments only one of the sugars of the sugar solution to a hydroxyl-carboxyl acid; and converting the hydroxy-carboxylic acid to a product.

21. The method of any one of claims 3-20, further comprising one or more of
      a) . processing the polymer by a method selected from injection molding, blow molding and thermoforming;
      b) . combining the polymer with a dye or pigment;
      c) . comprising grafting a molecule to the polymer, optionally wherein the molecule is selected from a monomer or a polymer;
      d) . treating the polymer with a peroxide, heating above about 120 °C, irradiation and combinations thereof;
      e) . further comprising shaping, molding, carving, extruding and/or assembling the polymer into the product, optionally, wherein the product is selected from the group consisting of personal care items, tissues, towels, diapers, green packaging, compostable pots, consumer electronics, laptop casings, mobile phone casings, appliances, food packaging, disposable packaging, food containers, drink bottles, garbage bags, waste compostable bags, mulch films, controlled release matrices, controlled release containers, containers for fertilizers, containers for pesticides, containers for herbicides, containers for nutrients, containers for pharmaceuticals, containers for flavoring agents, containers for foods, shopping bags, general purpose film, high heat film, heat seal layer, surface coating, disposable tableware, plates, cups, forks, knives, spoons, sparks, bowls, automotive parts, panels, fabrics, under hood covers, carpet fibers, clothing fibers, fibers for garments, fibers
      2014256918 05 Apr 2018 for sportswear, fibers for footwear, surgical sutures, implants, scaffolding, and drug delivery systems.
